{"messages": [{"type": "human", "data": {"content": "Is it safe to travel to Colombia right now?", "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "human", "name": null, "id": null, "example": false}}, {"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"tool_calls": [{"id": "call_CSRi4hB8KVyvo9DzcGHRxorX", "function": {"arguments": "{"country":"Colombia"}", "name": "get_travel_advisory"}, "type": "function"}], "refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 19, "prompt_tokens": 1932, "total_tokens": 1951, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 1792}}, "model_name": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "system_fingerprint": "fp_395c203642", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "run--019e102c-7d1d-7ca3-a875-7b7f3e1c2509-0", "example": false, "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_travel_advisory", "args": {"country": "Colombia"}, "id": "call_CSRi4hB8KVyvo9DzcGHRxorX", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1932, "output_tokens": 19, "total_tokens": 1951, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}}, {"type": "tool", "data": {"content": "{
  "country": "Colombia",
  "us_advisory": "Prepare for your trip toColombiaby reviewing theStateDepartmentTravelAdvisory, entry and exit requirements, local laws, andU.S. embassy tips. ReconsidertraveltoColombiadue to crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping, and natural disasters. Some areas have an increased risk. Read the entireTravelAdvisory.DoNotTravelto: Arauca, Cauca (excluding Popayán), Valle del Cauca (excluding Cali) and Norte de Santanderdepartmentsdue to crime and terrorism. Within 10km/5mi of theColombia-Venezuela border region due to crime ... Colombiatrip planning got harder on March 31,2026, when theU.S.StateDepartmentreissued itsLevel3advisoryand explicitly folded natural disasters into a risk picture that already included crime, terrorism, unrest, and kidnapping. That does not make allColombiaitineraries unworkable, but it does change how travelers should judge side trips, overland routing, and recovery plans outside ... TheUSStateDepartment'sLevel3advisoryisnota barrier totravel— it is a framework for informed decision-making. Business professionals who approachColombiawith structured protocols — verified transport, pre-arranged hotel pickups, domestic flights between cities, and disciplined nightlife awareness — will find Bogotá ... TheU.S.DepartmentofStateissued aLevel3traveladvisoryforColombiaon Tuesday, urging Americans to reconsider traveling there due to widespread crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping ...",
  "uk_advisory": "2 weeks ago -FCDO travel advice for Colombia. Includes safety and security, insurance, entry requirements and legal differences. March 17, 2026 -Before traveling to Colombia, run a free Colombia travel warning check to see the current safety score, active travel advisory warnings and entry requirements. Our live Colombia travel advisory warning is updated daily from the US State Department, UK FCDO, Australian Smartraveller and Canadian government. December 29, 2025 -FCDO travel advice for Colombia. Includes safety and security, insurance, entry requirements and legal differences. March 24, 2026 -You should think about your need to travel to this country, territory or region based on family or business requirements, knowledge of or familiarity with the region, and other factors. 1 week ago -The FCDO is warning against all but essential travel to certain regions of Colombia."
}", "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": null, "id": null, "tool_call_id": "call_CSRi4hB8KVyvo9DzcGHRxorX", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}, {"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Colombia is a country of vibrant culture and stunning landscapes, but it's important to be aware of the current travel advisories. The U.S. State Department has issued a Level 3 advisory for Colombia, urging travelers to reconsider their plans due to crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping, and natural disasters. Certain areas, such as Arauca, Cauca (excluding Popayán), Valle del Cauca (excluding Cali), and Norte de Santander, are particularly risky and should be avoided.

The UK Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) also advises against all but essential travel to certain regions of Colombia. It's crucial to stay informed and plan your trip with caution, especially if you intend to visit areas outside major cities like Bogotá.

If you decide to travel, consider structured protocols such as verified transport, pre-arranged hotel pickups, and domestic flights between cities to enhance your safety. Always stay updated with the latest advisories and make informed decisions based on your personal circumstances and familiarity with the region.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 204, "prompt_tokens": 2475, "total_tokens": 2679, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 0}}, "model_name": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "system_fingerprint": "fp_c0f910b5dd", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "run--019e102c-8865-7bb3-87c8-bf1ca759dafb-0", "example": false, "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2475, "output_tokens": 204, "total_tokens": 2679, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}}]}

